'''Kamo Shrine''' (賀茂神社) is a {{ill|Shrine|ja|神社}} located in {{ill|Tottori Prefecture|ja|鳥取県}} {{ill|Saiboku District|ja|西伯郡}} {{ill|Nanbu Town|ja|南部町 (鳥取県)|lt=Nanbu Town|lt_ja=南部町}} Yamato. Its former {{ill|Shrine Rank|ja|社格}} was {{ill|Gōsha|ja|近代社格制度#諸社|lt=Gōsha|lt_ja=郷社}} {{Sfn|鳥取県神職会|1935|p=474}}.

== History ==
The founding date is unknown. It is said that a {{ill|Branch Spirit|ja|分霊|lt=Branch Spirit|lt_ja=御分霊}} was transferred from Kyoto’s {{ill|Kamo Betsurai Shrine|ja|賀茂別雷神社}} and enshrined at the summit of Ōnaru-yama (大平山). Later it was moved to a place called Kobira on the mid-slope of the same mountain, and finally transferred to the foot of the mountain {{Sfn|鳥取県神職会|1935|p=474}}.

During the {{ill|Sengoku period|ja|戦国時代 (日本)|lt=Sengoku period|lt_ja=戦国時代}}, when {{ill|Amago Tsunehisa|ja|尼子経久}} controlled {{ill|Hōki Province|ja|伯耆国}}, the shrine was deeply revered; not only was an offering equivalent to 100 koku donated, but frequent visits, prayers, offerings, and shrine building were performed. However, with the downfall of the {{ill|Amago clan|ja|尼子氏}}, the shrine gradually declined {{Sfn|鳥取県神職会|1935|p=474}}. In the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代}}, in {{ill|1733|ja|1733rd year}} ({{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保}} 18), the lord of the {{ill|Tottori Domain|ja|鳥取藩}}, {{ill|Ikeda clan|ja|池田氏#鳥取藩主家|lt=Ikeda clan|lt_ja=池田氏}}, donated an additional 10 koku. In {{ill|1872|ja|1872nd year}} ({{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era}} 5) in April it was classified as a Gōsha, and on {{ill|February 3|ja|2月3日}} {{ill|1907|ja|1907th year}} (Meiji 40) it was designated as a {{ill|Shinsenheihaku Rikyō Shrine|ja|近代社格制度#神饌幣帛料供進社|lt=Shinsenheihaku Rikyō Shrine|lt_ja=神饌幣帛料供進社}} {{Sfn|鳥取県神職会|1935|p=475}}. It served as the tutelary shrine for the seven villages of {{ill|Inokoji|ja|猪小路}}, {{ill|Hokuhō|ja|北方}}, {{ill|Hara|ja|原}}, {{ill|Kobara|ja|小原}}, {{ill|Shinshō|ja|新庄}}, {{ill|Kami-Aga|ja|上阿賀}}, and {{ill|Shimo-Aga|ja|下阿賀}}, and was known as {{ill|Kamo Daimyōjin|ja|賀茂大明神}} until the early modern period {{Sfn|鳥取縣神社廰|2024}}.

In May {{ill|1916|ja|1916th year}} ({{ill|Taishō era|ja|大正}} 5), the unranked {{ill|Hokuhō Shrine|ja|北方神社}}—enshrined at Miyano-Tōge-yama in the Hokuhō district of {{ill|Ōkuni Village|ja|大国村 (鳥取県)|lt=Ōkuni Village|lt_ja=大国村}}—and the unranked {{ill|Kobara Shrine|ja|小原神社}}—enshrined at Kyakuno Mae in the same village—were merged with, on {{ill|April 30|ja|4月30日}} {{ill|1917|ja|1917th year}} ({{ill|Taishō era|ja|大正}} 6), the unranked {{ill|Aga Shrine|ja|阿賀神社}} (enshrined at Oga, Oji Kiriyama in the large district of Aga in {{ill|Tenshin Village|ja|天津村 (鳥取県)|lt=Tenshin Village|lt_ja=天津村}}) and the unranked {{ill|Tanabe Shrine|ja|田邊神社}} (enshrined at Towoben Kandō in the same village) through a {{ill|Shrine Merger|ja|神社合祀|lt=Shrine Merger|lt_ja=合併}} {{Sfn|鳥取県神職会|1935|p=475}}.

=== Shrine within the precincts ===
'''{{ill|Tadasu Shrine|ja|糺神社}}''' (ただすじんじゃ) is believed to have been founded at the same time as the main shrine, and together they were referred to as either '''{{ill|Kamo Ryōsha|ja|賀茂両社}}''' or '''{{ill|Kamo Shimokami Daimyōjin|ja|賀茂下上大明神}}''' {{Sfn|鳥取県神職会|1935|p=475}}.

'''{{ill|Sagi Shrine|ja|鷺神社}}''' (さぎじんじゃ) has an unknown founding date {{Sfn|石破|2000|p=31}}. It was originally enshrined at Watada Pass on the border of {{ill|Unpaku|ja|雲伯}}—a location commonly known as “Smallpox Pass”. It had long been venerated as the {{ill|Smallpox God|ja|疱瘡神}}, and served as a prayer site for the former lord {{ill|Ikeda clan|ja|池田氏}} {{Sfn|鳥取県神職会|1935|p=475}}. In October {{ill|1897|ja|1897th year}} ({{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era}} 30) the shrine building was destroyed by fire, but it was rebuilt in May {{ill|1905|ja|1905th year}} (Meiji 38). In {{ill|1916|ja|1916th year}} (Taishō 5) the {{ill|Tanaka Shrine|ja|田中神社}} of {{ill|Inokoji|ja|猪小路}} (enshrining deity: {{ill|Iwanagahime-no-mikoto|ja|イワナガヒメ|1=Iwanaga-hime|lt=Iwanagahime-no-mikoto|lt_ja=磐長姫命}}) was merged, and in {{ill|1917|ja|1917th year}} (Taishō 6) it was transferred from Watada Pass to the current precincts of Kamo Shrine {{Sfn|石破|2000|p=31}}.

== Enshrined Deities ==
;Main Deity
* {{ill|Betsurai-no-mikoto|ja|賀茂別雷命|lt=Betsurai-no-mikoto|lt_ja=別雷命}}
;Accompanying Deities
* {{ill|Emperor Jimmu|ja|神武天皇}}
* {{ill|Amaterasu Ōmikami|ja|天照大神|1=Amaterasu|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|lt=Amaterasu|lt_ja=天照大御神}}
* Toyoiwato-no-mikoto (at {{ill|Hokuhō Shrine|ja|北方神社}}: May Taishō 5; at {{ill|Aga Shrine|ja|阿賀神社}}: April 30, Taishō 6)
* {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主|lt=Ōkuninushi|lt_ja=大己貴命}} (at {{ill|Kobara Shrine|ja|小原神社}}: merged May Taishō 5)
* {{ill|Sukunabikona|ja|スクナビコナ|lt=Sukunabikona|lt_ja=少彦名命}} (at {{ill|Kobara Shrine|ja|小原神社}}: merged May Taishō 5)
* {{ill|Ukano Mitama|ja|ウカノミタマ|lt=Ukano Mitama|lt_ja=倉稲魂命}} (at {{ill|Tanabe Shrine|ja|田邊神社}}: merged April 30, Taishō 6)
* {{ill|Susanoo|ja|スサノオ|lt=Susanoo|lt_ja=素戔嗚命}} (at {{ill|Aga Shrine|ja|阿賀神社}}: merged April 30, Taishō 6)

